                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.104,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has our opinion this morning in case 13-1433 Brumfield v. Cain."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.104,
                        "stop": 202.728,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15131,
                            "name": "Sonia Sotomayor",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/sonia_sotomayor",
                            "last_name": "Sotomayor",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2776,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1249707600,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": null,
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2776"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32685,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 50379,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/sonia_sotomayor_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 2293,
                            "identifier": "sonia_sotomayor"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.104,
                                "stop": 14.687,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case comes to us from the Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.687,
                                "stop": 19.662,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Petitioner Kevan Brumfield was convicted of murder and sentenced to death."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.662,
                                "stop": 29.402,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Subsequently, this Court held in Atkins v. Virginia that the execution of the intellectually disabled contravenes the Eighth Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.402,
                                "stop": 39.627,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Brumfield sought an opportunity to prove he was intellectually disabled, but the Louisiana State Court rejected his appeal -- his request."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.627,
                                "stop": 44.31,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Brumfield then filed the petition for habeas corpus in federal court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 44.31,
                                "stop": 55.383,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "To secure relief Brumfield was required to show among other things that the State Court\u0027s decision was based on an unreasonable determination of the facts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.383,
                                "stop": 58.119,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The District Court found that it was."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.119,
                                "stop": 77.749,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Then, relying on new evidence, the District Court determined that Brumfield is intellectually disabled, but the Fifth Circuit reversed, holding that Brumfield had failed to show that the State Court\u0027s rejection of his Atkins claim was based on an unreasonable determination of the facts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 77.749,
                                "stop": 81.487,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We vacate and remand for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.487,
                                "stop": 92.256,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "To obtain a hearing in State Court, Brumfield needed only to point to evidence raising a reasonable ground to believe him to be intellectually disabled."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.256,
                                "stop": 112.614,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The State Court\u0027s refusal to grant him such a hearing was premised on two underlying factual determinations, that his reported IQ test result of 75 was inconsistent with intellectual disability and that he had failed to provide any evidence of adaptive impairment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.614,
                                "stop": 117.532,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The first of these determinations we conclude was unreasonable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.532,
                                "stop": 120.951,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "All IQ test results have a margin of error."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.951,
                                "stop": 129.336,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Accounting for this margin of error, Brumfield\u0027s 75 was squarely within the range of intellectual disability."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.336,
                                "stop": 134.442,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The State Court\u0027s second factual determination was also unreasonable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 134.442,
                                "stop": 163.097,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Brumfield pointed to ample evidence of his adaptive impairments including trial testimony that he had been at risk of neurological traumas at birth, was diagnosed with a learning disability and placed in special education classes, was committed to mental health facilities and given powerful medications, reads at a fourth-grade level, and simply cannot process information."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.097,
                                "stop": 178.812,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Accordingly, we hold that the State Court\u0027s decision was based on an unreasonable determination of the facts and that Brumfield was therefore entitled to have a Federal District Court consider his Atkins claims on the merits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 178.812,
                                "stop": 184.74,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Fifth Circuit is vacated, and the case is remanded for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 184.74,
                                "stop": 196.624,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has filed a dissenting opinion in which the Chief Justice, Justice Scalia, and Justice Alito joined acceptance to Part 1C."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 196.624,
                                "stop": 202.728,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has filed the dissenting opinion in which the Chief Justice joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
